entry.title: Introduce CompressionDictionaryTransportRequireKnownRootCert flag
entry.content:
We are observing potential issues with CompressionDictionaryTransport

feature that may be caused by network appliances that intercept network

traffic.



To investigate this issue, this CL introduces a new feature flag named

CompressionDictionaryTransportRequireKnownRootCert. If this feature is

enabled, Chromium will use stored shared dictionaries only when the

HTTPS connection's certificate is rooted by a well known root CA or when

the server is localhost.

entry.title: Add helpers for resolving *-position for BackgroundImageGeometry
entry.content:
Add ResolveXPosition() and ResolveYPosition() to help handle resolving

a *-position value to an "absolute" value - applying the edge affinity

etc. This keeps the knowledge in a single location. Convert current uses

to use the helpers when resolving *-position values.



This mean snapped and unsnapped values (i.e the available width/height)

are not mixed when computing positions. In some cases - no-repeat - the

edge affinity used snapped/unsnapped while any percentages were resolved

using snapped. This may lead to (likely minor) differences in rendering.

entry.title: Exclude HeuristicSource::kLegacy from non-active patterns
entry.content:
A HeuristicSource describes a mechanism to get heuristic predictions,

which is currently either ML or regexes. Due to pattern provider,

which can provide different regex definitions, "regexes" is split

further into different PatternSources.



The active HeuristicSource defines the mechanism that's used to compute

the fields' heuristic types used in production (the one that will

influence the overall type used for filling).



The non-active HeuristicSources are defined as the set of all available

HeuristicSources, except the active HeuristicSource. The PatternSources

among these non-active HeuristicSources are used to compute shadow predictions for the kAutofillParsingPatternProvider experiment.



What exactly all available HeuristicSources are depends on build flags

and feature flags, and this CL changes that definition.



Generally:

- HeuristicSource::kMachineLearning is only available when

kAutofillModelPredictions is enabled.

- HeuristicSource::kDefault, HeuristicSource::kExperimental and

HeuristicSource::kNextGen are only available in Chrome branded builds

when kAutofillParsingPatternProvider is enabled.

- HeuristicSource::kLegacy is always available.



This CL removes HeuristicSource::kLegacy from the available patterns in

Chrome branded builds when kAutofillParsingPatternProvider is enabled.

This is desirable for a few reasons:

- Chrome branded builds with kAutofillParsingPatternProvider are not

using the kLegacy patterns, not even for shadow metrics. They are

intended to be lower-quality regexes for non-Chrome branded builds.

- Since they are currently part of the non-active HeuristicSources,

they take up additional computational resources during parsing.



Bug: 1479353

entry.title: Remove incorrect CHECK() in ProfileTokenQuality
entry.content:
ProfileTokenQuality::GetObservationTypeFromField(field) is called at

submission and receives a field with autofill_source_profile_guid() set,

meaning that the field was autofilled with the profile of GUID

*autofill_source_profile_guid() at some point before. The logic

distinguishes between two cases:

- field.is_autofilled is true: The user accepted the autofilled value as

is.

- field.is_autofilled is false: The user edited the field since it was

filled with the aforementioned profile.



In the second case, the code currently CHECK()s that

field.previously_autofilled() is true. This serves simply as

"documentation" what this case is about, but is not relied upon in any

way. However, it turns out that this CHECK() is not guaranteed:

- When the user manually edits a field, BAM::OnTextFieldDidChangeImpl()

sets the field's is_autofilled to false and also updates its

previously_autofilled property. In this case, the CHECK() works fine.

- When Javascript modifies the value,

BAM::OnJavaScriptChangedAutofilledValueImpl() is called instead. In

this case, neither is_autofilled nor previously_autofilled are

changed. (see crbug.com/1506559)

At form submission, is_autofilled is still false though, since it is

reextracted from Blink. Since previously_autofilled is not stored in

Blink, it remains false, causing the CHECK() to fail.



Ultimately, this is a bug in the behavior of previously_autofilled.

Changing it is not trivial though, since a lot of metrics rely on it.



For now, to unblock the ProfileTokenQuality rollout, this CL simply

removes the CHECK().



Fixed: 1506195

entry.title: Fix incorrect lifetime of view in PopupViewViewsTest
entry.content:
Before, the view was created as a unique_ptr and destroyed in TearDown.

This behaviour doesn't mimic the one in production.

In order to fix this, the view is now created using "new" and it manages

its lifetime itself.



This change also brings a few modifications in the PopupBaseView

destruction flow.

Now, the destructor is designed to handle the case where the widget is

destroyed before the delegate (which was the case in the tests).

Theoretically, this cannot happen in production at the moment, but it

does not pose any disadvantage to handle this case (especially that

there is a chance this case might occur in the future in production

too).

entry.title: Fix number returning functions simplifications in multiplication
entry.content:
Currently, the code to move to CalculationExpression and back from it

assumes that multiplication is only in form of:

number * something or something * number

but sometimes number can be a math functions, and in that case

the code would call raw DoubleValue() on the math function,

resulting in sign(10%) to evaluate 10% as 10.



It's not noticeable in case of sign most of the time,

but with new number producing functions like progress*(),

which computes a number that can be based on percentage or relative

units, the difference would be very noticeable.



So, this CL treats number as possibly a math function, providing

conversion data to resolve against.

entry.title: Ruby: Fix invalid layout tree generation
entry.content:
This CL fixes a bug that LayoutRubyBase can have anonymous blocks and an

inline-table as children.



LayoutRubyBase is a subclass of LayoutBlockFlow, and it doesn't allow to

mix blocks and inline-level objects.



Root cause:

When a table-internal box is added to LayoutRubyBase,

LayoutBlockFlow::AddChild() assumed it as a block box, but

LayoutObject::AddChild() creates an inline-table wrapper for it.

LayoutBlockFlow::AddChild() moved existing inline children to an

anonymous block.



Fix:

We should make sure LayoutRubyBase doesn't create anonymous block

children. LayoutBlockFlow::AddChild() correctly assumes table-internal

boxes as inline boxes for LayoutRubyBase parents.



Now we can remove anonymous box handling in LayotuObject::AddChild(),

which was added by crrev.com/1225797



Bug: 1503372

entry.title: Prerender: Refactor CancelHosts / CancelAllHosts
entry.content:
This CL

1) decouples the implementation of canceling normal hosts and canceling

new tab host to separate functions into CancelHostInternal /

CancelNewTabHostInternal.

2) allows CancelAllHosts to use these functions (so that all

cancellation functions eventually use them).



This CL is intended for refactoring for subsequent CL (more

specifically, 1) to call only new tab cancellation, and 2) to reduce

codepoint to modify cancellation logic), and not intended to change

current behavior. Note that CancelAllHosts now additionally performs

NotifyCancel and ReportMetrics, but the current cancellation reason of

CancelAllHosts will be one of {kTabClosedWithoutUserGesturekStop,

kMemoryPressureAfterTriggered, kPrimaryMainFrameRendererProcessCrashed,

kPrimaryMainFrameRendererProcessKilled, kMemoryPressureAfterTriggered},

and current NotifyCancel and ReportMetrics will not handle this.

Therefore, this modification has no effect on current behavior.

This CL is separate from the main CL (https://crrev.com/c/4929491).

in following CLs. Thus, guarding these functions by the flag is

This CL updates "Parsing" layer for non-special URLs.

addressed in following CLs.

entry.title: Never break at a resumed parallel block flow inline node.
entry.content:
What I did in CL:5063008 caused trouble, because incoming child break

tokens could be re-propagated twice; once in BoxFragmentBuilder::

AddBreakBeforeChild(), and then again when walking through the

unprocessed incoming inline break tokens in BlockLayoutAlgorithm::

Layout().



Revert the code changes from that CL, and replace it with something

better (and simpler): Never consider breaking before a resumed inline

node in a parallel block flow. This is similar to how we already handle

interleaved block formatting context roots. They may also be interrupted

by floats that got pushed from an earlier fragmentainer, and thus not be

able to resume and place anything in one fragmentainer, and try again in

the next. See e.g. web_tests/external/wpt/css/css-break/float-005.html



Bug: 1506393
